-- German Green Party Passes Social Democrats for First Time, Forsa Poll Says
-- B y   M i k e   G a v i n
-- 2010-10-06T05:16:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-06/german-green-party-passes-social-democrats-for-first-time-forsa-poll-says.html
Germany’s Green Party gained one
point to to 24 percent, passing fellow opposition party the
Social Democrats in public support for the first time, according
to a Stern-RTL poll. The Social Democrats fell to 23 percent.  Chancellor Angela Merkel’s Christian Democrats and their
CSU Bavarian allies gained one point to 31 percent, while their
FDP coalition partner stayed at 5 percent, according to the
poll, carried out by Forsa.  Support for the oppositon Left Party was unchanged at 10
percent, the poll said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
